<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="F" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Far-off" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Far-off,</orth> adj. distant: <cit><quote>one might see those f. eyes look sad,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 1386" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1386</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>like f. mountains turned into clouds,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 4.1.193" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. IV, 1, 193</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>if we did but glance a f. look,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.1.10" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 1, 10</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>spies a f. shore,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 3.2.136" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C III, 2, 136</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>